<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 9:17AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTIOUS TRAVEL IS ADVISED FOR REDUCED VISIBILITIES FROM
SNOWFALL THIS MORNING...
WEATHER...
* Snowfall will impact portions of Southeast Michigan during the
morning commute.
* Isolated snow accumulations of up to one half inch are possible
this morning.
* Air temperatures will range between 32 and 36 degrees which
will limit roadway accumulations.
* Northwest winds around 15 mph with gusts to 20 mph.
IMPACTS...
* Snow will cause reductions of visibility to less than one
mile at times. There may be rapid fluctuations of visibility.
* Snowfall will lead to some slick spots, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps, and overpasses.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* The combination of snow and near-freezing temperatures will
result in localized slippery conditions and variable traffic
rates, mainly due to reduced visibility. Motorists are urged to
use caution and allow extra travel time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
